{"tid":463220,"cid":18,"subCid":0,"title":"PHILOSOPHY OF LANGUAGE","createTime":"2017-11-09T09:36:30.000Z","updateTime":"2017-11-09T20:57:00.000Z","uid":157469,"like":0,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":2,"replies":[{"pid":"8e8f7b0b58ddedb1653fe6aaed8e569379e760c9","tid":463220,"uid":157469,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T09:36:30.000Z","msg":"有無高手可以講 major problem of referential theory of meaningregarding a certain class of singular<br />\nterm &amp; Frege's puzzle for referential theories of meaning? <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"220af22f19d38e7b3d6cedcc06aee82fe8d905cb","tid":463220,"uid":126973,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T12:11:52.000Z","msg":"<blockquote>有無高手可以講 major problem of referential theory of meaningregarding a certain class of singular<br />\nterm &amp; Frege's puzzle for referential theories of meaning? <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n功課呀？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n一般入門書會話Referential Theory: <br />\n處理唔到 negative existentials (i.e., Pegasus never existed.)<br />\n處理唔到 names of fictional chactacter (i.e., James Moriarty is bald.)<br />\n處理唔到 referentially opaque context <br />\n(Frege's epistemic puzzle of identity就係想展示呢一點)"},{"pid":"c67864657e0a9c9e6763ee3e83c00e7d72def6a8","tid":463220,"uid":126973,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T12:25:38.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>有無高手可以講 major problem of referential theory of meaningregarding a certain class of singular<br />\nterm &amp; Frege's puzzle for referential theories of meaning? <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n功課呀？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n一般入門書會話Referential Theory: <br />\n處理唔到 negative existentials (i.e., Pegasus never existed.)<br />\n處理唔到 names of fictional chactacter (i.e., James Moriarty is bald.)<br />\n處理唔到 referentially opaque context <br />\n(Frege's epistemic puzzle of identity就係想展示呢一點)</blockquote><br />\n<br />\n嚴格來講，Frege's epistemic puzzle of identity唔係針對referential theory<br />\n佢係針對 Leibniz&rsquo;s Law (i.e., x = y &sup; (&phi;(x) &sup; &phi;(y))<br />\n<br />\n1. a=b  (比如話，晨星 = 暮星）<br />\n2. K(a=a)  （i.e, 我知道 a = a)<br />\n根據 Leibniz&rsquo;s Law, 可以得出&quot;<br />\n3 K(a=b)   （我知道晨星是暮星，但如果「我」係一個古希臘人，我就唔會知呢一點）<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nFrege嘅結論係，要放棄 Leibniz&rsquo;s Law <br />\n不過一般語言哲學書會講，referential theory  會面對Leibniz&rsquo;s Law一樣嘅問題 <br />\n因為 referential theory 認為 「晨星」同 「暮星」指涉同一樣嘅野，<br />\n所以兩者嘅意義一樣<br />\n而傳統 referenetial theorists 會認為兩個同等意義嘅 terms 係可以 interchangable without changing the truth value<br />\n而 Frege 就話 K(a=a) 同 K(a=b)唔係邏輯上等值"},{"pid":"c71d5a790ea722a88b5299926fdab13880932a1e","tid":463220,"uid":126973,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-09T12:46:23.000Z","msg":"<blockquote><blockquote>有無高手可以講 major problem of referential theory of meaningregarding a certain class of singular<br />\nterm &amp; Frege's puzzle for referential theories of meaning? <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /></blockquote><br />\n<br />\n功課呀？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n一般入門書會話Referential Theory: <br />\n處理唔到 negative existentials (i.e., Pegasus never existed.)<br />\n處理唔到 names of fictional chactacter (i.e., James Moriarty is bald.)<br />\n處理唔到 referentially opaque context <br />\n(Frege's epistemic puzzle of identity就係想展示呢一點)</blockquote><br />\n<br />\n不過呢D 唔係 conclusive嘅反駁<br />\nMeinongnian 會話 negative existentials, fictional names 係支持緊有 non-existent entities"},{"pid":"7712418b183b802cf5d6bcc434330b85e6a3da58","tid":463220,"uid":157469,"like":0,"d